I have a custom field called 'Target Release' which is of type 'multi version picker' so it provides us with the various release version value Names as options to select in the drop down. 
When conducting an advanced search the returned information under the 'Target Release' column displays the 'release version value Name' (perfect - exactly what I want), however if you display that saved filter within a wiki page using the jiraissues macro it displays the 'release version value ID' within the 'Target Release' column.

Example of macro on the wiki;
{jiraissues:title=Theme/Epic/Story within Sprint17|columns=type;key;summary;component;status;assignee;sprint;Target ReleasefixVersion;Story Points;Epic Link;rank|url=https://jira.COMPANYXYZ.com/jira/sr/jira.issueviews:searchrequest-xml/20533/SearchRequest-20533.xml?tempMax=1000}

As the 'release version value ID' information is not intuitive and doesn't provide any relevance to the Name it is not found to be valuable to the End Users. So can we make this configurable or have it display the name please.

This is related to a similar issue I raised previously GHS-10132 where the Sprint value shows as an ID rather than the name.

