h3. Expected behavior
Disabling the "random mode" of wallboard slideshow will make the slides appear in a pre-defined order.

h3. Actual behavior
Slides will be displayed in a random order, however, it will keep that order for subsequent loops.

h3. Steps to reproduce
# Setup the *Wallboard Slideshow* to display at least 3 dashboards;
# Start the *Wallboard Slideshow*;

h3. Additional Notes
Thanks _Johnny_ for sharing the outcome of the below steps.
* Refreshing the web page *does not* help;
* Clearing the browser's cache *does not* help;
* Closing the tab and reopening it *sometimes* help;

Additionally, I made some additional troubleshooting.
* This *does not* relate to the fact that the random order was defined once before. The same was reproduced on a clean _6.4.2_ instance;
* *Sometimes* it will display the slideshow in the correct order, but there's no pattern on this;
* You can clearly see the flag {{random=false}} on the URL;

